Police say they've conducted a full investigation on the matter and found that no crime had been committed. JOHANNESBURG - Authorities say the case involving a woman who tried to sell her three-year-old grandson has been handed over to social workers in KwaZulu-Natal. Police say they've conducted a full investigation on the matter and found that no crime had been committed. It's understood the grandmother tried to sell the child at a store in Verulam for R2,000 before authorities intervened. The police's Thulani Zwane says: “The mother of the three-year-old child was also present and she took the child from the grandmother.” (Edited by Shimoney Regter)